The expert’s strategy is to repeatedly select and click on a cell containing a 'token' that is adjacent to a contiguous vertical cluster of 'token' cells, always choosing the uppermost or leftmost token in the cluster. Each action targets the next available 'token' at the edge of the cluster, proceeding in a top-to-bottom (or left-to-right, if applicable) order, systematically removing the entire connected group one by one until none remain. The expert never clicks on 'empty' cells or isolated tokens unless they are the last remaining in a cluster, and always acts on a token that is directly adjacent to the remaining cluster, ensuring the cluster shrinks in a controlled, sequential fashion.

The game dynamics observed are as follows: when a 'token' cell is clicked, not only is that token removed (cell becomes 'empty'), but all contiguous (vertically or possibly horizontally adjacent) 'token' cells that are part of the same cluster are also removed in a single action, or the cluster size decreases by a fixed amount. However, in these demonstrations, each click only removes the selected token, and the cluster size decreases by one per action, indicating that only the clicked token is removed per step. The process continues until all tokens are removed from the grid, with the cluster size decreasing accordingly. The game is deterministic, and the only allowed action is to click on a cell containing a 'token' that is adjacent to the current cluster.